### Identity Server API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5218
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Health Check - Get Swagger
GET {{baseUrl}}/swagger/index.html

### 2. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userName": "testuser",
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "Test@123456",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

### 3. Login with username
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userNameOrEmail": "testuser",
  "password": "Test@123456",
  "rememberMe": true
}

### 4. Login with email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userNameOrEmail": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "Test@123456",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 5. Get current user info (requires token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Register - Test validation error (empty fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userName": "",
  "email": "",
  "password": "",
  "firstName": "",
  "lastName": ""
}

### 7. Register - Test duplicate username
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userName": "testuser",
  "email": "another@example.com",
  "password": "Test@123456",
  "firstName": "Another",
  "lastName": "User"
}

### 8. Login - Test wrong password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "userNameOrEmail": "testuser",
  "password": "WrongPassword123",
  "rememberMe": false
}

